# UI Tokens

Every color, spacing, radius, and type ramp used in code MUST resolve to a
named token. If a Figma value has no matching token, **add it to the
source-of-truth file first**, then use it.

## Source of truth

The authoritative tokens live in code, not in this Markdown file:

- **CSS variables & `@theme`**: `{{UI_PACKAGE}}/styles/globals.css` (Tailwind v4
  CSS-first setup) — adjust path if your project stores styles elsewhere.
- **Legacy Tailwind preset**: `{{UI_PACKAGE}}/styles/tailwind-preset.ts` (only
  if still used).

This file is an **index**, not a mirror. Keep the namespaces below in sync
with the CSS; do not duplicate every value.

## Namespaces (index)

| Namespace | Example class | Where defined |
|---|---|---|
| `text-*`           | `text-text-primary`, `text-text-secondary`, `text-muted-foreground` | `globals.css → @theme` |
| `bg-*` / `border-*`| `bg-neutral-subtle`, `border-neutral-strong` | `globals.css → @theme` |
| status colors      | `text-success`, `text-info`, `text-warning`, `text-destructive` | `globals.css → @theme` |
| spacing            | Tailwind default unless `@theme` extends it | `globals.css` |
| radii              | `rounded-sm`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg` | `globals.css → @theme` |
| typography         | font family, weights, size ramps | `globals.css → @theme` + `tailwind-preset.ts` |

## Rules

- **CRITICAL**: no hex, no rgb, no arbitrary Tailwind values (`text-[#fff]`,
  `p-[13px]`). All values route through `@theme` variables.
- **CRITICAL**: if a Figma value has no token, open `globals.css`, add it to
  `@theme`, commit that change, and only then use it in feature code.
- **ENFORCED**: prefer semantic token names (`text-text-primary`,
  `bg-neutral-subtle`) over raw palette names (`text-slate-900`).

## Migration note

If you're updating this file in an already-running project, do NOT copy the
full token list here. Keep the index above and trust the CSS file.
